  "prompt": "Which kind of guitar should I buy as an amateur?",
  "response": "As an amateur, choosing the right guitar can be a bit overwhelming due to the many options available. Here are a few factors to consider and some recommendations that might help you make an informed decision:\n\n### Factors to Consider:\n\n1. **Type of Music**: Consider the genre of music you want to play. Different styles may suit different types of guitars.\n   - **Acoustic Guitars**: Great for folk, country, and softer genres.\n   - **Electric Guitars**: Ideal for rock, blues, and jazz.\n   - **Classical Guitars**: Best for classical and flamenco music.\n\n2. **Budget**: Determine how much you're willing to spend. There are good options at various price points.\n\n3. **Size and Comfort**: Make sure the guitar feels comfortable in your hands. If you have smaller hands, consider a guitar with a narrower neck.\n\n4. **Sound and Tone**: What kind of sound are you looking for? Acoustic guitars have a warm, natural tone, while electric guitars can offer a wide range of sounds through amplifiers and effects.\n\n### Recommendations for Amateurs:\n\n#### Acoustic Guitars:\n1. **Yamaha FG800**:\n   - **Price**: Around $200 - $300\n   - **Why**: Great build quality, solid tonewoods, and a rich sound that's excellent for beginners.\n   \n2. **Fender CD-60S**:\n   - **Price**: Around $200\n   - **Why**: Reliable, affordable, and a good choice for beginners with a comfortable neck and solid sound.\n\n#### Electric Guitars:\n1. **Squier by Fender Stratocaster**:\n   - **Price**: Around $200 - $300\n   - **Why**: A classic design, affordable, and versatile sound that's great for various genres.\n   \n2. **Epiphone Les Paul Special II**:\n   - **Price**: Around $200\n   - **Why**: Durable, great sound, and a comfortable playability that's perfect for rock music.\n\n#### Classical Guitars:\n1. **Yamaha C40**:\n   - **Price**: Around $150 - $200\n   - **Why**: Affordable, good sound quality, and a comfortable playability that's great for beginners.\n\n2. **Cordoba C5**:\n   - **Price**: Around $300\n   - **Why**: Higher quality tonewoods, excellent for those interested in classical music.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Try Before You Buy**: If possible, visit a music store to play different guitars. This will help you find the one that feels and sounds best to you.\n- **Accessories**: Consider purchasing a gig bag, picks, a tuner, and perhaps some beginner lessons to get started.\n- **Future Upgrades**: Start with a budget-friendly option and upgrade as you progress in your skills.\n\nChoosing the right guitar as an amateur should be about finding a balance between affordability, playability, and the type of music you enjoy. Happy playing!",
